name: Caesarium Cadmide
description: A dark-golden hued alloy composed of cadmium and caesium.  Often confused with tritanium due to its tint.  An essential ingredient in various composites and condensates.

name: Carbon Polymers
description: A synthetic carbon compound created from raw hydrocarbons and silicate rock materials.  Important ingredients in a variety of carbon- and gel-based composites.

name: Ceramic Powder
description: A fine powder synthesized from various natural gases and solids through reactant processes.  Used as a strengthening agent in both armor plating and shield generators, as well as constituting an important part of many other composite materials.

name: Crystallite Alloy
description: A polynuclear heterometallic compound created from cobalt and cadmium.  Crystallite alloys are a fundamental building block in the creation of crystalline composites.

name: Dysporite
description: Quicksilver mixed with dysprosium forms the soft but extremely resilient dysporite, an amalgamatic alloy which plays a key role in most advanced sensor and reactor technologies.

name: Fernite Alloy
description: An intensely durable and extremely versatile alloy, Fernite, when combined with certain other materials, is a crucial stepping stone in the creation of a whole host of advanced technologies.

name: Ferrofluid
description: Ferrofluids are superparamagnetic fluids containing tiny particles of magnetic solids suspended in liquid.  The primary component in the creation of ferrogels.

name: Fluxed Condensates
description: When combined with other materials and alloys, fluxed condensates help contribute to a unique quantum state highly conducive to efficient reactor operation.

name: Hexite
description: A chemical compound, formed through electrosporadic oxidization of chromium and platinum.  Has a wide range of applications in the production of advanced technology and is highly sought-after by industrial manufacturers.

name: Hyperflurite
description: Hyperflurite is one of the most radioactive substances known to man.  Composed of a mixture of radioactive metals and raw hydrocarbons, this luminescent goop provides catalysis for a variety of generative and reactive machine processes.

name: Neo Mercurite
description: A silvery, shimmering liquid compound, Neo Mercurite is a crucial element in many forms of advanced sensor and processor technology.

name: Platinum Technite
description: An intensely resilient alloy composed of platinum and technetium.  Highly sought-after in the machinery and armament industries.

name: Promethium Mercurite
description: A metallic radioactive compound, Promethium Mercurite emits a faint green glow visible to the naked eye. It is a crucial part of a new generation of processors and capacitor units being developed by the Amarr Empire.

name: Prometium
description: A highly radioactive cadmium-promethium compound, used as a catalytic agent in the manufacturing of thrusters, reactor units and shield emitters, among other things.

name: Rolled Tungsten Alloy
description: An extremely strong compound, made from tungsten rolled in a sheath of platinum.  A crucial component in the creation of carbides which have a wide field of utility in the manufacture of various equipment.

name: Silicon Diborite
description: A mineral composite which, in large quantities, gives off a distinct crystalline glow.  When combined with other composites, is usable for a variety of manufacturing purposes.

name: Solerium
description: When chromium and caesium are combined with raw silicates in the proper proportions, Solerium is created.  Since its initial discovery, Solerium's uniquely shifting dark-to-bright red hue has prompted poet and musician alike to create hymns in praise of its uniquely shifting deep red hue.

name: Sulfuric Acid
description: A strong mineral acid, used in many chemical reactions and production processes.  One of the most widely used chemicals in history.

name: Thulium Hafnite
description: Despite its unremarkable gray appearance, Thulium Hafnite has proven to be extremely effective as shielding against electromagnetic radiation and free neutrons. It is a valuable component in the production of processor and capacitor technologies, especially in the Gallente Federation.

name: Titanium Chromide
description: Titanium Chromide is in high demand among technicians and manufacturers for its unique combination of strength, light weight and catalytic potential.
